content: A thoroughly entertaining app that I worked on for about a month or two and enjoyed every second of it. Bravo

This game made my no no place very stiff and made my pants not fit right for a whole 20 minutes, and I do not appreciate the chafing feeling I got when I was trying to walk up the stairs in my home. I can't give this more than 5 stars but I would if I could to try to show how many stars I saw when I tripped over my afflicted thingie and fell down the stairs and hurt my head.
Great puzzles. Great interface.

Puzzle 40 hint 5 is bs!!!!! Other than that Awesome app and puzzles but it's hard to see notes and x's with the darker themes. Please change note colors on dark themes. Some of the hardest puzzles are too dang hard lol

Love the app, third one of the series I've finished and bought kickstarter. One feature request - summarize the time spent on puzzles somewhere, wanted to see just how long I got out of the $4.99 but it'd be mental math to check
Great puzzle game that forces you to think a different way. I just wish there were more levels!

I love it!! I mean, I can't give anything else than 5 stars to thermo sudoku either, but I've saved the last levels of sandwich because they are just so much fun =) I hope you make a sandwich sudoku 2!
Level 40 is the first time I've tried to use hints. They don't seem to actually guide you though. There are some assumptions I'm just not understanding how to jump to. Enjoying the game though.
I love the app! The games are challenging and great sandwich Sudoku's. The app itself is well-designed and works great.

I really like this app. Well worth the price for puzzles set by humans. I do wish that I could sort the puzzle orders by difficulty. I also find the clues as difficult to decifer as the puzzle sometimes
Amazing stuff. Best sudoku apps in the store

Great puzzles. Some are solvable in no more than 10 minutes while others require complex thinking skills and a deep understanding of the puzzle. There are free hints to every puzzle (if needed) and the marking options are very helpful. Definitely recommend the app as well as the creator's youtube channel (cracking the cryptic).
Absolutely love it
Loving this! I made it thru Classic Suduku by Cracking the Cryptic and this is a great next step. App is well designed and makes it easy to mark cells.
Nice puzzles. But the app heats my phone too much and uses too much power. It's like I solve 2 puzzles and my phone has already half of the power that had. You guys should optimize that.
Brilliant puzzles
Great app
My favorite variation of sudoku and this app absolutely nails it. So fun to play and challenging puzzles.

Good high quality puzzles, but the app drains battery very fast. Which is not great when travelling. Also, the app unnecessarily opens in full screen mode, hiding the system's notification bar and menu buttons.
100% handmade puzzles. No computer generated ones. Best series of apps around.

Really nicely done and supports landscape now. The puzzle selection screen could be improved to reduce scrolling but that's minor. The only thing I wish it had was notifications for when there are new puzzles.
Wonderful spin on Sudoku. Hints sometimes seem to ignore possibilities which make them hard to understand. Also quite the battery drain which shouldn't be needed for the simplistic graphics it uses.

I hate the fact that I'm stuck at playing only one type of puzzle. 20€ for having 4 different apps in my phone is too much. When I bought this I did not realize it was exclusive sandwich and I had to buy 3/4 different apps for different puzzles. Even the app itself is not the greatest. Bad design and HUGE battery comsuption. Only reason I'm not giving a 1 star rating is due to the fact that I actually enjoy solving the puzzles.. Unfortunately all other aspects are extremely negative to me.
Great game great controls

The game is great, the hints are sometimes inscrutable, but the reason I give it 4 stars is it chews through battery life faster than games with far more graphical fidelity going on. Why? Probably Unity. This game is not at all graphically intense, so I'm guessing it's engine stuff in the background. But I can play this game for 30 minutes and lose double the battery life I do with Arknights, for example. Hope they optimize that in the future.
I usually really enjoy the puzzles from you all, but there was a bi-value universal grave in puzzle 18, which isn't fun to deal with.
Very challenging variant
Great game, nothing to complain about gameplay-wise! Minor UI bug: The stars in the menu is hidden behind the camera on Samsung S10+.
Can't wait for more Sudoku puzzles! Sandwich Sudoku is my favorite so far but I'm excited to try all their apps
Excellent. Simple and intuitive interface, good difficulty progression, satisfying puzzles, no manipulative marketing or in app purchases.

This is the best interface for sudoku I've played. The puzzles are hand crafted and fun to solve. The hints could use some work. Often there are not enough or they aren't explained how they came up with the digits.

Unity is just too power hungry and frankly is overkill for making a Sudoku app. I won't be buying any of the other sudoku apps by this group which is unfortunate since I find their puzzles to be excellent.
Fantastic app. The hints teach you how to think instead of just showing a random number. Truely a piece of art.

Just picked up the app and I'm loving the twist on Sudoku so far! One suggestion I have regarding the interface is that when tapping on the sandwich sum, please remove the sliding animation. I frequently gray out the sums when I'm done with them, but the sliding animation takes up a couple seconds each time and it's a minor annoyance.

Was having a great time until I found two puzzles that seemingly would not complete. I reached out to the dev studio to submit a bug and he responded VERY promptly and pointed me to the fallacious logic that was causing my actual heartburn. HIGHLY recommend all their sudoku apps!
Literally a perfect app for Sudoku. All of the tools needed to solve the puzzles efficiently, and easy to use. No complaints!
Great way to learn sandwich sudoku, one of my favourite variants!
World class puzzles with a world class solving interface. Top shelf!
Great construction. Very challenging and enjoyable.
Beautiful handcrafted puzzles with great hints.
Fantastic app and fantastic channel. Keep it up Simon!
Discovered the creators through their YouTube channel. Not surprised about the high quality sudokus they've delivered with this app.
Outstanding game
Great sandwich sudoku app. Wonderful YouTube channel.

This app works well, but I've found too many instances of ambiguous solutions. I end up having to put in a number to see which way the app wants the solve to go. It's really frustrating coming from a group that takes pride in quality puzzles.
very good i love it

Contains what's on the package. A few bugs though. I'm struggling to reproduce it reliably, but if you have pencil marks it occasionally gets stuck and won't let you change to full sized numbers. (Eventually if you change number modes enough times it sorts itself out.) Would also love it if a tap in empty space (off the puzzle) unselected whatever was selected on the board, regardless of what that was. Five stars with minor bug fixes and a little quality of life upgrading.
An excellent new dimension to an ancient puzzler, sleek design, great interface, hugely enjoyable.
Very well set puzzles! I only wish the app loaded quicker.

I enjoy these puzzles a lot, they are very challenging. The only thing I don't like is that the puzzle disappears as soon as you enter the final, correct number. No time to admire your handiwork! Maybe it could instead just stop the clock at this point and flash up a fanfare. Or at least, make this an option! Do this and I'll give you the 5th star!
Loving the variation

This variation is so cool. Love the youtube channel. However, the controls leave something to be desired, and there is no dark theme (as in sudoku board is black, numbers are a light color). A dark theme would be easy to add, and as for the controls, what i'm really missing is an input method with the numbers selected first, where I can pick a number and now any cell I touch is auto-filled, instead of selecting the cell and then filling it in.
This is a wonderful variant that there isntenough of.
Not many apps for sandwich Sudoku and the controls are really good.
Love this app! A fun twist on sudoku.
Numbers are too close together.
Great app
Very very satisfying puzzles

Great game, lovely handcrafted puzzles. Could use some extra quality of life tweaks, such as ability to preview current state of a saved puzzle without opening it, or sort by recently played or difficulty. The stability suffers a little, sometimes the app does not start couple times in a row or closes after quick change to another one. One significant bug I found is that hiding sum options (which numbers can add up to target) is not undone by "undo" button.
A fun variant of sudoku, very entertaining and challenging
A brilliant app, with very interesting puzzles, created by some very passionate puzzlers!
Great puzzles and good interface. The puzzles aren't just random sudokus, they have clearly been designed and tested. Looking forward to more!
Amazing.
This is a very well made app

Very nice puzzles with a clear and steady difficulty increase. The timer further enables you to see your progress across time, went from 35+min for easier puzzles to 15min for hard ones - absolutely stunning app!

Love the handcrafted puzzles created for this app, thanks for the hard work Mark and Simon. My only criticism is that it is tedious to input numbers near the end of the puzzle. It would be a great quality of life addition to allow us to hold a number then place that number throughout the grid.
The dudes behind the app are wonderful people. I am really happy to support them by buying their apps. Eagerly waiting for the Chess Sudoku.
Addicting
Great game. The numbers could be larger.
Great sukoku app!
Excellent hand crafter goodness

Great app with great puzzles, if the hints make no sense you just are basically asking for a hint too soon and you are missing something obvious. Just wish it wasn't as draining on my battery as it is.

The puzzles are very nice, and they get more difficult at the right pace. I didn't find the hints too helpful, perhaps because I got stuck at different parts of the puzzle than the creators were anticipating. Overall, very satisfying solves. The app could have had bigger input numbers (1-9). There's a big unused space nearer the top of the screen. The grid could be shifted up to make room. The digits are smaller than keyboard characters for text/email. "Fat finger" errors common and annoying.

The game is very well laid out and fun though I do have a few issues with it. Firstly: it would be nice to do a multi pencil marking style. When I try to do corner pencil markings and middle markings, it just overwrites it. Making it hard to do double notation as per your cracking the cryptic videos. Secondly: I found puzzle 12 to have two different forms of ambiguous solutions surrounding the numbers 2,3 and 4. I input the numbers and verified that the puzzle should work either way.
I need more puzzles here and on the other app. I will trade you kidneys for more puzzle

Very good. Progress through the puzzles is excellent and helps you get better and develop new techniques for solving the later puzzles. Interface is excellent. Couple of small things stopping it from getting 5 stars. 1. I'd like it if the game reopened on the puzzle you were last playing. Mainly because... 2. Clicking PLAY defaults to #1, rather than the highest unsolved puzzle. 3. Would be good if the game could prevent screensaver kicking in. Annoying when studying & screen goes black.
Great app, great YouTube channel. This is my way of supporting them. Btw if you don't like getting cheats-like advice on whatever you place incorrectly, go to the options menu
Fantastic sudoku experience and controls
Fantastic app, reignited a joy for Sudoku, 10/10
Amazing interface and well crafted puzzles

Very intuitive app. Puzzles are extraordinary and satisfying to solve. Only encountered a bug once (and I got rid of it by fiddling with the different buttons). Only QoL change I would suggest is : When clicking the Play button, opening the page on the next solvable puzzle (or the ongoing one if there is one) instead of opening on the top of the page. Cheers and congrats on the great application.
Amazingly well designed puzzles. Sandwich Sudoku is a very fun variant and nice change of pace from the classic sudoku. I can't wait for all 100 puzzles to be released!
Excellent app with rather difficult puzzles and flexible annotation system.
Excellent puzzle game with good range of difficulties from fairly easy to very hard
Everything about the app is great. Hoping we can get special puzzles such as the Mozart Sandwich Sudoku etc. Would be nice to have a section to try these out.
Awesome app, one of the best. Pure class!
Good twist
Awesome hand made challenging puzzles.
Fantastic hand set puzzles and love the variant! Won't find this quality of Sudoku anywhere else
Very fun and engaging game. Puzzles are well designed.
Amazing app! Love the puzzles and your videos :-)
Really enjoying this app
Worth the price
Great sudoku app; I'm looking forward to more puzzle types from Cracking the Cryptic and Studio Goya!
Excellent software design. Challenging puzzles!
Doesn't work, impossible to solve
Great puzzles! Uses more battery than I'd like.

The app takes a little getting used to, but I don't know if it can be improved. It's just hard to get used to any kind of phone controls for a Sudoku app. The puzzles are all well designed, and being familiar with the creators' YouTube channel, I'm sure they're all handpicked and vetted. Maybe even handmade. Highly recommend.
Great game!! Please make a lot more puzzles!!
Great puzzle app
Very good app, allows you somewhat easy starter levels and then drives into some really hard levels. Overall very good!

Easily the best Sudoko based game on the app store. Most innovative controls, easiest app to use, and with, in my opinion, the best options for pencil marks! Having played many of the (free) sudoku apps, this beats all of them. Would love if you guys made a single app with loads various variations on Sudoko (Sandwich, Killer, Thermomer, etc). I personally would be happy to have in app purchases per variations.
Really interesting puzzle, the levels are nicely handcrafted by people who love puzzle solving. There's always an enjoyable logical path to solve them without the need to guess.
Many hours of sudoku fun! Works like a charm. Well worth the price!

Has been waiting forcthis for a long time and its my favorite sudoku variant! One small suggestion about the UI design: it might work better if you change the mode switch icons smaller and the number pads larger, I find sometimes clicking wrong numbers. Another thing is when you are at stage selection page, it seems a waste of space to only have 2 columns and dragging the page too long, it would make more sense to have more columns and make the square smaller to fit more in a page.
Most enjoyable form of Sudoku and this app is well designed for easy selection of alternatives. A few more levels per month would be nice as I'll soon run out of games.
Really great interface and puzzles, but I'm having some pretty horrendous battery usage from the app. Hopefully there's a solution?
Great game
Very intriguing puzzles that feel so good to solve! Excellent customer service and quick response when I had an issue. Great game, great app, highly recommended!!
I love this game. Ran into some uniqueness problems earlier but they were due to my own blindness. Upping to 5 stars ^^
Good fun so far. But puzzle 6 does not have a unique solution. 356&7 are ambiguous in subsquares 3456&9.

Great game, screen works really well. Challenging, goes from easy-ish to hard, nice progressive training method. Couple of suggestions - maintain cursor position after undo. Increase contrast within selected cell so that pencil marks easier to read in low light .

I've had a thoroughly absorbing time playing these handmade Sudoku puzzles. My one recommendation to anyone thinking of playing would be to go into the settings and turn off error highlighting. Having mistakes pointed out immediately took away some of the enjoyment for me, that is trying to work out where I've gone wrong.
A fantastic App.
Just like the Youtube series: amazing.
Great fun... Looking forward to more "levels"

Love this game. The cryptic guys definitely thought this through, but then I would have expected no less. There are occasions where I have to hit a number button multiple times before it is registered in a cell. There needs to be more contrast between a selected number and shaded boxes, rows and columns. Multicolor themes with a color on the top interfere with the sandwich numbers across the top of the grid. Fix the button glitch and give more contrast and I will give the game 5 stars.
Great and fun alternative to sudoku. Interface is simple to use, and provides the tools needed. Wish there were more puzzles.
Love the channel! Fun game. Here is my support.
Great app! Puzzles are great so far and have a nice solution path. Only minor improvement suggestion is to be able to put both corner and central markings in a cell (like the CTC web app)
Excellent app. Worth the money especially as there are no in app purchases or adverts to annoy you.
love your channel. love your new app. hoping you will make new variant sudoku app soon.
A great app! I love the sandwich sudoku style of puzzle and this is a great app to play them. Thanks so much!
Brilliant for Sudoku aficionados!

Only played the first puzzle so far, but a very solid app. Great responsive interface with all the tools you'd want in solving a puzzle, plus nice features like highlighting where a selected digit appears in pencil notation. Can't think of anything I'd change, great work guys!
Fantastic! Has all the tools to make solving a little easier.
Great app. Couple of minor things but I am sure they will be fixed soon. Looking forward to many hours of entertainment.
